{"docs": [{"idx": "chunk-e349346689a80f3ecd76ea41d5c92ac8", "passage": "Marie Curie was a Polish-born physicist and chemist. She was born in Warsaw, Poland in 1867. Curie moved to Paris to study at the Sorbonne University. She conducted research on radioactivity and discovered the elements polonium and radium.\n\nMarie Curie married Pierre Curie, a French physicist. Together they won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1903. She later won a second Nobel Prize in Chemistry in 1911. Their daughter Irene Joliot-Curie also became a famous scientist.", "extracted_entities": ["Marie Curie", "Polish-born", "physicist", "chemist", "Warsaw", "Poland", "1867", "Paris", "Sorbonne University", "polonium", "radium", "Pierre Curie", "French physicist", "Nobel Prize in Physics", "1903", "Nobel Prize in Chemistry", "1911", "Irene Joliot-Curie", "scientist"], "extracted_triples": [["Marie Curie", "was", "Polish-born"], ["Marie Curie", "was", "physicist"], ["Marie Curie", "was", "chemist"], ["Marie Curie", "born in", "Warsaw"], ["Marie Curie", "born in", "Poland"], ["Marie Curie", "born in", "1867"], ["Marie Curie", "moved to", "Paris"], ["Marie Curie", "studied at", "Sorbonne University"], ["Marie Curie", "conducted research on", "radioactivity"], ["Marie Curie", "discovered", "polonium"], ["Marie Curie", "discovered", "radium"], ["Marie Curie", "married", "Pierre Curie"], ["Pierre Curie", "was", "French physicist"], ["Marie Curie", "won", "Nobel Prize in Physics"], ["Marie Curie", "won", "Nobel Prize in Chemistry"], ["Marie Curie", "won in", "1903"], ["Marie Curie", "won in", "1911"], ["Irene Joliot-Curie", "was", "scientist"], ["Marie Curie", "has daughter", "Irene Joliot-Curie"]]}, {"idx": "chunk-b42061bebcddff064478cc227c79fce1", "passage": "Albert Einstein was a theoretical physicist who developed the theory of relativity. He was born in Ulm, Germany in 1879. Einstein worked at Princeton University in New Jersey. He won the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921. His famous equation is E=mc^